I come to you bearing a gift--the gift of origami club. I am posting daily challenges for beginners, intermediate folders, and advanced practitioners. I would love to see you rise to the challenge and post pictures. Feel free to post your own challenges as well. Classroom codes will be emailed to you so you can join in on the fun.

May the folds be ever in your favor!

Best,
Kiyomi Wilks

*Please use Google Classroom to access this NEW club!

Hello, Explorers!
We submitted a proposal to present at the National Charter Schools Conference this summer! There is open voting for the public, so we would LOVE if you all could vote a "thumbs up" for our proposal:
No More Homework! How Frontloading can Drive Academic Progress for Innovative Charter Schools (#29255857) You can vote here by making a simple, free account: https://conference.publiccharters.org/FORMS/SESSION_SELECTOR/cfp_login.php?formid=29265862&speakerid=29255794

More about the conference in the link below. Have a great long weekend, everyone!

A new order will go out this week (for delivery in four weeks or so), so now is the time to place orders if you're in need of some long sleeve t-shirts or sweatshirts/hoodies/zip-ups.
Remember, you can always layer any long sleeve shirt or sweater under an Explore shirt while in the building if you don't have cold weather Explore gear.

Hello, Explore families!
Just a few quick transportation reminders -
1. If you have not cleared your browser history in a while, there is a chance that the pdf with Transportation Routes on our website is an older version trapped by your browser. Just clear your history and your device should then access the most current version that is posted.
2. Bus routes have really smoothed out over the last two weeks. But, if you have any questions or concerns, please email us at transportation@exploreacademy.org.
3. We are attaching images of each route here so that you can save to your phone for easy access to times and stops
Have a great rest of your week, everyone!

post_text:
Explore families who utilize bus transportation-

There are still some lingering issues with a few routes. Inevitably, the first few weeks of every school year are an adjustment period as drivers work with new bus stops, traffic patterns, construction, etc. At present, students from some routes are still not arriving on time and some routes will need new or altered bus stops for safety and/or student need.

Please be patient as we work with the transportation company to adjust the routes to be as convenient as possible while still arriving safely and on time.

We really appreciate your understanding, flexibility, and patience.

Calling all Explorers... It's almost time for school!

Orientation for 6th, 7th, 9th, and transfer students will take place Thursday, August 16, and Friday August 17. Check your contact email for details and your orientation time slot. Don't forget your chromebook and charger. Parents, please bring your child's documents with you (immunizations, birth certificate, transcripts, test scores, etc.)

School starts Monday, August 20. Bus routes were emailed out yesterday and will be adjusted over the next few weeks as the drivers run the routes.

We can't wait to see you all and kick off 2018-2019 with a bang!

post_text: A group of Explore Academy students participated in a project with the Albuquerque Philharmonic Orchestra, creating work in response to a selection of music that will be played at the APO's spring concert. Student work from Explore Academy and several other metro area schools will be displayed in the lobbies of both performance spaces and projected over the stage during both concerts. Performances are free to the public and will be held on Friday, March 4th at Immanuel Presbyterian Church in Albuquerque and on Sunday, March 6th at the V. Sue Cleveland High School concert hall in Rio Rancho. Both shows start at 7:30 pm. Below are just a few student works.

post_text:
Students -

For those of you who have picked up your PowerSchool credentials, you can now log on and see your schedule.

There were a couple of classes that got dissolved over the summer, so check your schedule for gaps. If you find any, schedule an appointment with Ms Barreras to enroll into a class. If she doesn't see you in time to fix the problem, report to the front office during that timeframe for instructions.

If the schedule doesn't look correct in any other way, please let me know immediately!

Don't have your PowerSchool credentials yet, and wondering where to be on Monday? Check your inbox - the schedule was automatically mailed to you after choosing the courses.
